[Norovirus infection continues to cause problems
for companies operating cruise liners on both
sides of the Atlantic. While this may reflect a
simultaneous seasonal increase in prevalence of
norovirus infection in northern Europe and North
America, other factors cannot be excluded
entirely. The investigation conducted by the
magazine "Which?", invoking "freedom of
information" legislation, has revealed disturbing
lapses in hygiene in specific cases. Generally ,
however, the disinfection procedures developed by
cruise ship operators have been effective and
allowed the rapid turn-around of ships without
any enhanced risk to passengers and crew. In
general the frequency of outbreaks of norovirus
infection on cruise liners is probably no greater
than in other situations where people from
diverse backgrounds are brought into close
proximity (e.g. hospital wards, schools, recreational camps, etc).
Consequently these reports of norovirus infection
affecting passengers on cruise liners will be
discontinued for the present. - Mod.CP]
